{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Wire store-wide overlap step into _run_plan_review (LLM-gated, graceful skip, advisory surfacing)\n\n## Why\nThe overlap check must fire in the tolerant window before claim — during plan review — and fold its results into the plan-review output as advisory coaching, WITHOUT ever blocking the claim or altering the claim-gate verdict. This is the integration seam tying Cupid enrichment + retrieval + judge into the agent workflow.\n\n## What\n- Integrate in `_run_plan_review` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:401` — the real post-pass site where rising-floor/completion-floor/sidecar/signing run; NOT the public wrapper `review_plan` at :352). Sequencing is critical: inject overlap findings BEFORE `coverage['counts']` is baked and BEFORE the sidecar emit + attestation signing, so `advisory_surfaced` count and the signed manifest include them consistently (or, explicitly, keep overlap findings in a SEPARATE `overlap[]` verdict key excluded from the advisory cap and from the signed coverage counts — chosen approach: a separate `overlap[]` key so the ≤3 overlap items never displace real plan-review advisories under the cap, and the attestation is unaffected).\n- Steps: synchronously extract the query ticket's digest from the already-assembled full-text context (S1), run `retrieve` (S5), run the pairwise `judge` (S6); attach the ≤3 results to the verdict's new `overlap[]` array (each item = the S6 finding incl. its `rebar link` command). Update the `--output text` renderer `_render_plan_review_text` (`src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py:386`) to print the `overlap[]` section, and include `overlap[]` in the MCP `review_plan` result + its output schema.\n- LLM-gate / graceful skip: if the `[agents]` extra, plan-review, or API key is absent, the step is a silent no-op (no `overlap[]`, no error, claim proceeds). RUNTIME failures too (S1/S5/S6 exception, retrieval timeout, judge error, empty candidates) are caught → empty `overlap[]`, logged, never block.\n- Config: `verify.overlap_enabled` (default OFF, on `VerifyConfig` `[tool.rebar][verify]` alongside `require_plan_review_for_claim` — where all gate flags live) gates the whole step independently of the plan-review gate.\n\n## Dependencies\nS1 (enrich), S5 (retrieve), S6 (judge). These are prerequisite sibling stories under this epic; this story is the integration and can only be completed once they land (sequenced last).\n\n## Scope\n- Edits: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py` (`_run_plan_review` injection), `src/rebar/schemas/plan_review_verdict.schema.json` (add `overlap[]`), `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py` (`_render_plan_review_text`), the MCP `review_plan` output model, `overlap_enabled` on VerifyConfig `[tool.rebar][verify]`; write the architecture ADR `docs/adr/NNNN-cross-ticket-overlap.md` (the epic's ADR deliverable is owned HERE).\n- OUT: the component ops (S1/S5/S6), async corpus enrichment (S2/S3/S4).\n\n## Testing\n- Unit `tests/unit/test_plan_review_overlap.py` (FakeRunner + fixture corpus): overlap findings land in `overlap[]`; the claim-gate verdict/`advisory_surfaced`/attestation are UNCHANGED by overlap findings (assert byte-identical signed coverage vs a run with overlap disabled); `[agents]`/key absent → no `overlap[]`, verdict identical; a judge exception → empty `overlap[]`, no raise; `overlap.enabled=off` → step skipped; `overlap[]` appears in both CLI text and MCP JSON.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `review_plan` returns ≤3 overlap findings in a dedicated `overlap[]` key (each with a `rebar link` command); the claim is NEVER blocked and the signed claim-gate coverage/attestation is byte-identical to a run with overlap disabled; verified by `pytest tests/unit/test_plan_review_overlap.py::{test_surfaced,test_verdict_unchanged}`.\n- [ ] The query digest is generated at review time from the ticket's current full text (independent of the ticket being in the enriched corpus).\n- [ ] `[agents]`/plan-review/API key absent → silent no-op, verdict identical to before; a runtime failure in S1/S5/S6 → empty `overlap[]`, logged, never blocks; verified by `::{test_graceful_skip,test_runtime_error}`.\n- [ ] `overlap.enabled` (default OFF) gates the step independently; `overlap[]` is rendered in CLI `review-plan --output text` and present in the MCP `review_plan` result + output schema.\n- [ ] Integration site is `_run_plan_review` (:401), with overlap findings in a separate `overlap[]` key so they never displace real advisories under the cap.\n- [ ] The architecture ADR `docs/adr/NNNN-cross-ticket-overlap.md` is written (the epic's ADR deliverable).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783573468782992001,"uuid":"690e3da1-836f-416d-81bc-45ea6eebc179"}